The course deals, first and foremost, with the issues of web surveys that are different from other survey modes (CAPI, CATI, etc). The focus will be on the advantages and disadvantages of web surveys, the possibility of integrating web surveys with other survey modes, sample formation, devising and setting up the questionnaire for a web survey and response rate issues. The practical part of the course allows students to devise the research design of a web survey and set up the survey on the internet. The course takes place in a hybrid form, i.e. students can participate in lectures and practicals either in the classroom or via internet.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The goal of the course is to give an overview of the planning and carrying out of web surveys. Successful participation in the course gives the student basic theoretical knowledge of web surveys and a hands-on experience in designing and carrying out a web survey.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  A student having passed the course successfully -	has basic knowledge on the methodology of web surveys; -	knows the central issues and possible solutions of web survey research design; -	can apply the acquired knowledge to planning a web survey and setting up a web questionnaire.
